DOM - Document object model
---------------------------
1. What is the use of DOM in JavaScript?
   DOM stands for Document Object Model. 
   It is a programming interface that allows us to create, change, or remove elements from the document. 
   We can also add events to these elements to make our page more dynamic. 
   The DOM views an HTML document as a tree of nodes.

DOM METHODS
-----------
1. document.getelementsByTagname('tagname')
2. document.getElementById('id')
3. document.getElementByClass('class')
4. document.querySelector('#id/.classname/tagname') ------- get one element
5. document.querySelectorAll('#id/.classname/tagname') ---- get collection of elements
   